    <note>Hu(1) Xian(2) [11872] Recommended by xiang (xianggong) entered the imperial university during Shaoxing (1131-1162)--probably earlier end. At this time the Cheng(1) brothers [3102] [3105] scholarship was prohibited. He secretly learned its explanation (shuo) with Liu(2) Mianzhi [11864] and studied the Yi Jing with Qiao(2) Ding [24399]. Late in life, he received an office (i.e. after death of Qin(1) Gui [8008]). His only son died prematurely. Lin Zhiji, WJ, 18.1a-5b; Zhu Xi, WJ, 97.15a-17a; Zhou Bida, WJ, 35.12a-14b; Fujian TZ, 148.26a. CBD, 2, 1577-8.</note>
